{
  "id": "infiniflow_ragflow_15735",
  "repo_name": "infiniflow/ragflow",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow",
  "base_commit": "6bf7056422837db69c00ff073ce992716bd44399",
  "pr_number": 15735,
  "issue_number": 15611,
  "issue_title": "[Feature Request]: Normalize model-family detection for reasoning extraction",
  "issue_body": "### Self Checks\n\n- [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues), including closed ones.\n- [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Non-english title submitions will be closed directly ( \u975e\u82f1\u6587\u6807\u9898\u7684\u63d0\u4ea4\u5c06\u4f1a\u88ab\u76f4\u63a5\u5173\u95ed ) ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields.\n\n### Is your feature request related to a problem?\n\nYes. Some providers expose Qwen reasoning models with provider-prefixed names, for example `qwen/qwen3-8b` in the SiliconFlow config. RAGFlow's fallback reasoning parser only recognizes model family `qwen3`, so provider-prefixed Qwen names can skip the `<think>...</think>` extraction fallback and leave reasoning text inside the normal answer.\n\nThe relevant code path is:\n\n- `internal/entity/model.go` derives model class from the substring before `-`, so `qwen3-8b` becomes `qwen3`, while `qwen/qwen3-8b` becomes `qwen/qwen3`.\n- `internal/entity/models/common.go` only extracts inline reasoning for exact `qwen3`.\n- `internal/entity/models/gitee.go` and `internal/entity/models/siliconflow.go` call `GetThinkingAndAnswer` as the fallback when `reasoning_content` is absent.\n- `conf/models/siliconflow.json` includes provider-prefixed Qwen models such as `qwen/qwen3-8b`.\n\n### Describe the feature you'd like\n\nNormalize model-family detection before fallback reasoning extraction, so names or classes such as `qwen3-8b`, `qwen/qwen3-8b`, and case-varied Qwen names are treated consistently as Qwen3-family models.\n\nThis should keep the visible answer free of inline `<think>...</think>` content when thinking is enabled and the upstream response does not include a separate `reasoning_content` field.\n\n### Describe implementation you've considered\n\n- Add a small nil-safe helper in `internal/entity/models` that normalizes provider-prefixed and case-varied model names/classes to parser families such as `qwen3`.\n- Use that helper inside `GetThinkingAndAnswer`, so existing Gitee and SiliconFlow fallback callers benefit without changing provider routing.\n- Add unit tests for `qwen3-8b`, `qwen/qwen3-8b`, and case-varied Qwen names.\n- Add provider-level regression tests for inline `<think>` extraction in Gitee and SiliconFlow chat responses.\n- Keep the change scoped to reasoning extraction; avoid changing unrelated model discovery or routing semantics.\n\n### Documentation, adoption, use case\n\nThis improves answer formatting for reasoning-capable Qwen models and avoids exposing inline reasoning tags in user-visible answers.\n\n### Additional information\n\nI searched open and closed issues/PRs for `SiliconFlow qwen3 thinking`, `GetThinkingAndAnswer qwen`, `qwen/qwen3 <think>`, and `SiliconFlow reasoning_content qwen`, and did not find an exact duplicate.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-08T11:32:19.000Z",
